MOTORISTS are being warned of a city centre road closure beginning today. Water work warning for city drivers MOTORISTS are being warned of a city centre road closure beginning today.Scottish Water are working at George Square to repair a waste water main, and have advised drivers of a one-lane closure at Queen Street.Pedestrians are also being advised of a footpath closure between St Vincent Place and George Square.The water firm has vowed to complete the work as quickly as possible, but have warned further road traffic management may be needed in other areas of the square.They thank those affected for their understanding while the work is undertaken. 